RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 42. Maiden Special Weight Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. The Top Three Accredited Texas Bred Finishers Will Receive $4,500, $3,500 and $2,000 respectively. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RB MOTHERLOAD was well rated while three wide, advanced on the turn then edged clear in late stretch to prevail in the end. PEARLS COMET AA vied for the lead while four wide then emerged from the pack to duel with an inner rival throughout the turn, gained the short lead in the early stretch then was out finished by an outer rival in the end. AA BURNING TEMERITY saved ground early then was gaining in late stretch and was best for third place. COLOR ME GONE MHF vied inside then moved up to lead the way in late backstretch, then dueled with an outer rival on the turn, was used up in the stretch and tired in the end. ERIN MHF chased the pace while four wide then rallied leaving the turn but came up flat in the stretch. WMA TORCH LIGHT broke inwardly then settled inside, bid mildly on the turn and was no threat in the end. RB MAMA WINGATE vied for the lead while five wide and outside of rivals down the backstretch, settled back on the turn then continued to flatten out in the stretch. UPTOWN KEEPMEINMIND settled in the two path in the early furlongs and remained no threat in the end. WMA WILD ROSES vied for the lead while two wide then faded after the half. WMA BANDANA vied for the lead while three wide then stopped after the half.
